<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="53" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,618,2039]" pageId="4" pageNumber="53">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,281,618,644]" pageId="4" pageNumber="53">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Male: Eyes not approximate, face and frons with parallel sides; vt present; legs mainly yellow, except CxII and tarsi; pulvilli not developed, claws present; wing membrane with a transverse brown spot; abdominal Tg 
<number box="[318,361,693,719]" pageId="4" pageNumber="53" value="3.5" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="2.0">2–5</number>
with lateral yellow spots; St 
<number box="[705,718,693,719]" pageId="4" pageNumber="53" value="8.0">8</number>
without striking bristles. Surstylus with a drop-like spine at apex; hypandrium enlarged apically.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
